          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The a-particle detector is a twin-gridded",
                "ionization chamber.The distances from the cathode to",
                "grid, grid to anode, and anode to shield were 61.0,",
                "15.0, and 9.0 mm. The working gas of the ionization",
                "chamber was a mixture of Kr + 2.82% CO2 with 1.0-atm",
                "pressure. High voltages applied on the cathode, grid,",
                "and anode were -1500, 0, and +750 V. The distance",
                "from the cathode of the chamber to the center of the",
                "deuterium gas target was 16.3 cm. A 238U(238U3O8)",
                "film sample was placed in the chamber at the other",
                "position of the sample changer to determine the",
                "absolute neutron flux by measuring the fission",
                "fragments. Isotopic abundance is 99.999%, thickness",
                "is 493.6 ug/cm2(238U only), diameter is 45.0 mm,",
                "backing is Ta sheet."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BF3"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The neutron flux monitor is a BF3 long counter.",
                "The axis of the BF3 long counter and the normal line",
                "of the electrodes of the ionization chamber were at",
                "0degree to the beam line. The distance from the front",
                "side of the long counter to the center of the gas",
                "target was 272 cm."
              ]
            }
          ],
